{
  "stem": "7415.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I will be living in places where there will be elevators, which go so fast, and some things which I felt were wonderful.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And next morning, when I woke up, I heard my mother crying.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I heard people were in our apartment.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I was lying there and heard that-- I was shocked that my mother was crying and that people were saying that my grandmother, at night had jumped from sixth floor to kill herself.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And I think that when-- that was 22nd of July, 1942.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And since then, all my bad memories started of war, real war.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Well, my mother came to me and told me that my-- that my grandmother left town, because many Jewish people in the ghetto were leaving town for concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But they didn't know that they were concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were told that they were going to work.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So that just my mother-- my grandmother left.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And she helped me to-- to get dressed quickly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then we never returned to this apartment.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we were really homeless.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We were living one day here, another day some other place.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The orphanage place was taken to the concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I never tried to tell my mother that I know that my grandmother died.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I was looking down, you know-- always wonder how a person can jump from such a height and kill herself, that it-- it must be awful.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But there were no other way to kill.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "There were no pills, or gas, or other things which she could do.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And it-- after we were homeless, it was like one day I remember that the Germans put us into a big line of people and were giving some numbers.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
